    <h2>Section A: Attempt any TWO questions:</h2><h3>Question 1</h3>
<div><p><p>How can  Horner’s rule be used to evaluate the f(x) and f(x) of a polynomial at a given point? Explain. Write an algorithm and program to calculate a real root of a polynomial using Horner’s rule.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Horner&#8217;s Rule:</p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-18119" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/horner.jpg?resize=594%2C542&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="594" height="542"></p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-18120" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/ex.jpg?resize=721%2C471&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="721" height="471"></p>
<p>Algorithm:</p>
<p>1 Read order of polynomial, say &#8216;n&#8217;.</p>
<p>2 Read coefficient of polynomial.</p>
<p>for i=0 to n</p>
<p>read a[i]</p>
<p>end for</p>
<p>3 Read point of evaluation, say x0.</p>
<p>4 Set b[n]=a[n]</p>
<p>5 Compute</p>
<p>for i = n-1 to 0</p>
<p>b[n-1]=a[n-1]+b[n]*x0</p>
<p>end for</p>
<p>6 Print b[0] as result</p>
<p>7 End</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Program:</p>
<pre class="lang:c decode:true">#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main()
{
     float a[100],sum=0,x;
     int n,i;

     printf("\nEnter degree of the polynomial X :: ");
     scanf("%d",&amp;n);
     printf("\nEnter coefficient's of the polynomial X :: \n");
     for(i=n;i&gt;=0;i--)
     {
            printf("\nEnter Coefficient of [ X^%d ] :: ",i);
            scanf("%f",&amp;a[i]);
     }

     printf("\nEnter the value of X :: ");
     scanf("%f",&amp;x);

     for(i=n;i&gt;0;i--)
     {
        sum=(sum+a[i])*x;
     }

     sum=sum+a[0];

     printf("\nValue of the polynomial is = [ %f ]\n",sum);

     return 0;
}</pre>
</div>
